## The Refund Object

| Parameter  | Value |
|:-----------|:------|
| `object`        | *(string)* 'refund' |
| `id`            | *(string)* Refund ID |
| `livemode`      | *(boolean)* Whether this is a Live (true) or Test (false) refund. |
| `location`      | *(string)* Path to retrieve the refund |
| `amount`        | *(integer)* The amount in the smallest subunits of the currency used. So for `thb` (Thai Baht) you'll need to pass the amount in satangs. |
| `currency`      | *(string)*  The currency as its lower-cased international 3-letter code, defined by the [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) standard. |
| `charge`        | *(string)*  The charge ID that has been refunded. |
| `transaction`   | *(string)*  The transaction ID of the refund |
| `created`       | *(datetime, format: [iso8601](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601))* Creation date of the refund |

